I think scooters should be allowed in bike lanes. It’s safer for everyone, most scooters aren’t very visible and they don’t have adequate safety gear, so I’d like them to have a safe place to commute, and just coexist with bicyclists. *And they aren’t breaking the law if their scooter is 50ccs or under. That’s if the bike lanes have a 49cc limit, I don’t know the actual laws. The actual engine specs are usually “49cc” or something like that, and then the manufacturers just round it up to the next whole number in the product name. Same for motorcycles.
